JOHANNESBURG – Private education provider Advtech is reporting a massive increase in revenue in its tertiary education division. Its financial results showed a 26 percent rise in revenue, climbing to nearly R1,6-billion and contributing 39 percent to group’s revenue. Operating profit rose by 44 percent, reaching R321 million. But the group says operating profit from its school division declined by 13 percent, falling just below R300-million. READ: NSFAS welcomes govt decision to fund free education Advtech blames the losses on fraud and subdued student enrollment figures due to financial pressure on families and the impact of emigration. eNCA